  <infoaction message='Weapons

Like addons, weaponry can require hardpoints and/or expansion space.  There are two kinds of weaponry; Primary and Secondary:

Primary weapons will fire whenever you press the space bar, and will continue firing as long as you are holding it down.  If you have more than one firing weapon, one will fire and then after a short delay another will fire, and so on until they have all fired or one of your primary weapons is ready again.  Typically - but not always - primary weapons have unlimited ammunition.

Secondary weapons are weapons you can select from.  Only one secondary weapon can be fired at once.  You fire secondary weapons by pressing &apos;F&apos; and cycle through your choices with &apos;Q&apos;.   When you have a secondary weapon, you will see it and any ammunition it needs on the left side of the screen.

Some weapons need ammunition - this should be noted in most cases in the description.  Some weapons can take more than one kind of ammunition; like addons do to ships, ammunition can do things to weapons.  Some ammo may do less damage but have a longer range, for example.

To field-test your weaponry, proceed to the Medregg system.' tag='msg_explain_weapons' show_once_only='true' labels='' shown='false'/>
