  <infoaction message='Fuel

You&apos;ll see a new option on this planet for refueling - every time you jump, a certain amount of fuel is deducted from your total.  Planets allow you to replace this fuel... for a price.  

Addons

Addons are an easy way to customize your ship without having to buy a new one.  Each addon tends to do something for you, though often at the expense of something else.  The one for sale here will increase your speed, but take more fuel when jumping.  

Also, addons tend to require &apos;expansion&apos; space (your ship has some space set aside for internal modifications) or &apos;hardpoints&apos; (interfaces to outside systems).

To buy or sell addons, click the &apos;Addons&apos; button.  The interface is exactly the same as buying cargo.

Ships

Addons  can only take you so far - ships don&apos;t have unlimited expansion space or hardpoints.  You can buy a new ship by clicking the &apos;Shipyard&apos; button  on any planet that&apos;s selling ships.

When you&apos;re ready for the next tutorial, accept the &quot;Multi-Jump Tutorial&quot; mission.' tag='msg_explain_addon' show_once_only='true' labels='' shown='false'/>
