  <infoaction message='Advanced Mapping

As you&apos;ve likely noticed, there&apos;s more to the universe than even the two sectors you&apos;ve seen so far.  From here, we&apos;re going to jump to the Medregg system - it&apos;s labeled &apos;unknown&apos; because you haven&apos;t visited it before.  Usually, sectors you haven&apos;t visited will either not appear on the map or will only appear as &apos;unknown&apos;.

You can enter the map by pressing &apos;M&apos;.  There are two ways to put more than one sector on your itinerary:

(1) Select the Sol sector and press &apos;add to itinerary&apos;, like you did before for Alpha Centauri.  Then, click on the Unknown sector and press &apos;add to itinerary&apos; again, or
(2) Select the &apos;Unknown&apos; sector and press &apos;plot course&apos;.

The second method is the easiest, as the computer will plot a course for you, but the first one allows more fine-grained control over where you go.

When you&apos;re ready, jump to Sol. ' tag='msg_explain_multijump' show_once_only='true' labels='' shown='false'/>
